goals.question: What is the trend of population over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of year vs people
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the population has been increasing, decreasing or remaining constant over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of age in the population?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the age distribution of the population and if there are any age groups that are over or underrepresented.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution of the population?
goals.visualization: bar chart of sex vs people
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the gender distribution of the population and if there are any gender imbalances.

goals.question: What is the average age of the population?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of age in the population and if there are any outliers or extreme values.

goals.question: What is the population density in different years?
goals.visualization: choropleth map of year vs people
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the population density in different years and if there are any regions that have experienced significant changes in population over time.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['sex']).sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='sex', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['age'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['age'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average age of the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    chart.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Population Density')
    plt.title('What is the population density in different years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
